    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1975-02-24T14:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1975-02-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="274"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                <head>274. Memorandum of Conversation<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d274fn1"
                        >Source: Ford Library, National Security Adviser, Memoranda of Conversation,
                        Box 9. Secret; <gloss target="#t_Nodis1">Nodis</gloss>. The meeting took
                        place in the Oval Office at the White House.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            from="1975-02-24T15:00:00-04:00" to="1975-02-24T15:45:00-04:00"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date">February 24, 1975, 3–3:45
                            p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> Secretary General <persName>Joseph
                            Luns</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> Assistant Secretary General Jorg
                        Kastl</item>
                    <item>President <persName corresp="#p_FGR1">Gerald R. Ford</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Dr. <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>, Secretary
                        of State and Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs</item>
                    <item>Amb. <persName corresp="#p_RDH1">Donald Rumsfeld</persName>, Assistant to
                        the President</item>
                    <item>Amb. <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">David Bruce</persName>, Permanent
                        Representative to <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>
                    </item>
                    <item>Lt. General <persName corresp="#p_SB3">Brent Scowcroft</persName>, Deputy
                        Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs</item>
                </list>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion of matters other than the European security
                    conference or <gloss target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss>.]</p>
                <p>President: Do you have any thoughts on <gloss target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss>?</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_LJ12">Luns</persName>: The Soviet Union has proposed equal
                        reductions,<note n="2" xml:id="d274fn2">See <ref target="#d345fn5">footnote
                            5, Document 345</ref>.</note> which is not reasonable.</p>
                <pb facs="0842" n="807" xml:id="pg_807"/>
                <p>The tactical nuclear force issue<note n="3" xml:id="d274fn3">See <ref
                            target="#d357">Document 357</ref>.</note> is linked. Several of us are
                    nervous that you will weaken the shield. Your efforts seem to be strategic
                    weapons, but the problem in <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> is
                    tactical.</p>
                <p>I don’t think the Soviet Union will plan a war in <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss>. The outcome is too uncertain. I think the Soviet Union will
                    wait to see the outcome of <gloss target="#t_SALT1">SALT</gloss> and <gloss
                        target="#t_CSCE1">CSCE</gloss>. I think we are in the position that <gloss
                        target="#t_CSCE1">CSCE</gloss> will be a summit.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>: Thanks to the Europeans.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_LJ12">Luns</persName>: We must think about the possible
                    euphoria and guard against it.</p>
                <p>President: How about a Western Summit beforehand?</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_LJ12">Luns</persName>: I think it is a good idea. The
                    French were cool to the idea.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>: It is ridiculous to think the
                    East and West can meet and [as?] consumer and producer, but not the <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> allies.</p>
                <p>On the nuclear package, we won’t press it as our solution. It is up to the
                    Alliance whether it is to be presented to the Soviet Union.</p>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion of matters other than the European security
                    conference or <gloss target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss>.]</p>
            </div>
